Iranian Film `A Separation' Wins Golden Bear Top Prize at Berlin Festival

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   H i c k l e y
-- 
2011-02-19T18:52:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/iranian-film-a-separation-wins-golden-bear-top-prize-at-berlin-festival.html
The Iranian film “Nader and Simin,
A Separation” won the Golden Bear award for the best film at
the Berlin Film Festival. Directed by Asghar Farhadi, the film
tells the story of the end of a marriage.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Catherine Hickley at 
 chickley@bloomberg.net  